{{infobox Chinese|l=Yang Metal Dog|kanji=庚戌|romaji=kanoe inu|onyomi=kōjutsu|p=gēngxū|w=keng-hsü|mi=kɤŋ⁵³ ɕy|y=geng1 seot1|j=geng1 seot1|ci=kɪŋ sœt̚|mc=kæŋ syt|oc-bs=kˤraŋ ʔsuʔ}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}

'''Yang Metal Dog also known as 庚戌''' (kanoe inu (庚戌), koukin no inu (庚戌), koujutsu (庚戌)) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 47th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Kiyuu|ja|己酉|lt=Kiyuu}} and followed by {{ill|Shingai|ja|辛亥|lt=Shingai}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Kou|ja|庚}} represents yang {{ill|Metal|ja|金}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Dog|ja|戌}} represents yang {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, establishing a generating relationship ({{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|五行思想#相生（そうじょう）|lt=Mutual Generation|lt_ja=相生}}) (Earth generates Metal).

==庚戌の年==
A year in the {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦}} that leaves a remainder of 50 when divided by 60 is a {{ill|year|ja|年}} of {{ill|Kou-Inu|ja|庚戌}}.
