It is the 47th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Kiyuu|ja|己酉|lt=Kiyuu}} and followed by {{ill|Shingai|ja|辛亥|lt=Shingai}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Kou|ja|庚|1=Kanoe (庚)}} represents yang {{ill|Metal|ja|金}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Dog|ja|戌|1=Dog (zodiac)|lt=Dog (戌)}} represents yang {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, establishing a generating relationship ({{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|五行思想#相生（そうじょう）|lt=Mutual Generation|lt_ja=相生}}) (Earth generates Metal).

